3. SOVEREIGNTY PRINCIPLE
The LBH protocol is architected for distributed edge sovereignty. Users are encouraged to 
maintain the decentralized nature of the implementation. No party shall claim exclusive 
centralized ownership of the LBH specification itself.

4. ETHICAL INTENT STATEMENT (Non-Binding)
The author strongly discourages the use of this specification for:
- Intentional harm to civilian populations.
- Surveillance systems designed to violate fundamental human rights.
- Development of covert weaponized autonomous systems.
This clause expresses the ethical philosophy of the HormigasAIS community and the 
"Mesentery" connective framework.

5. PHILOSOPHICAL DEFINITION
The name “MESENTERY” represents the structural connective philosophy of HormigasAIS: 
A living system that connects, nourishes, and sustains distributed nodes without domination.

